content:
Regulations for SMS communication differ by country and carrier. Before setting up an SMS channel in Service Cloud Messaging, review your country's messaging regulations to avoid fines or blocked messages.

Available in: Lightning Experience. This article applies to Standard and Enhanced SMS channels, but not Messaging for In-App, Web, WhatsApp, Facebook Messenger, Apple Messages for Business, and Bring Your Own Channel.

Standard SMS channels are scheduled for retirement. Upgrade to Enhanced channels by February 14, 2026, to avoid service interruptions. Enhanced SMS offers features like session transfers and enhanced bot support.

You can use existing US or Canadian numbers for long code SMS channels or request a new in-country number from Salesforce. File a case with Salesforce Customer Support to create your channel. If required, attach country-specific messaging forms to the case.

To view your country's regulations, see SMS Regulations by Country (English only). Download any attached forms and review them carefully.
title: SMS Regulations by Country
